            <div class="https-explanation">
                <p>HTTPS (HTTP Secure) is the secure version of HTTP, the protocol over which data is sent between your browser and the website you are connected to. It's secured through the use of TLS/SSL.</p>
                
                <div class="https-steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div class="step-description">Your browser requests a secure connection with a website</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div class="step-description">The server sends its SSL certificate containing its public key</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div class="step-description">Your browser verifies the certificate with a Certificate Authority</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">4</div>
                        <div class="step-description">Your browser generates a symmetric session key</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">5</div>
                        <div class="step-description">This key is encrypted with the server's public key and sent to the server</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">6</div>
                        <div class="step-description">The server decrypts this using its private key to get the session key</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">7</div>
                        <div class="step-description">All further communication is encrypted with this shared session key</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="https-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits of HTTPS:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Data confidentiality:</strong> Information remains hidden from eavesdroppers</li>
                        <li><strong>Data integrity:</strong> Information cannot be modified during transfer</li>
                        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Users can trust they're communicating with the intended website</li>
                        <li><strong>Better SEO:</strong> Search engines favor HTTPS websites in rankings</li>
                        <li><strong>Required for modern features:</strong> Many new web features only work with HTTPS</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
