<div id="lesson4-3-content" class="lesson-container">
    <p class="mb-4">Blockchain technology represents one of the most significant applications of cryptography in recent years. A blockchain is a distributed, immutable ledger that records transactions across many computers. The technology combines several cryptographic principles to create a secure, transparent, and tamper-resistant system.</p>
    
    <div class="key-concept mb-5">
        <h4><i class="fas fa-key"></i> Key Concept</h4>
        <p>A blockchain is a chain of blocks containing information that is secured using cryptography. Each block typically contains a cryptographic hash of the previous block, transaction data, and a timestamp. The decentralized nature and cryptographic security make blockchains extremely difficult to modify once recorded.</p>
    </div>
    
